---
/**
 * Barbados Welcome Stamp (Digital Nomad Visa) - Long-form CRO-optimized page
 * Static page (overrides dynamic route for this specific country)
 */

import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", text: "Overview", level: 2 },
  { id: "quick-decision", text: "Quick Decision Guide", level: 2 },
  { id: "requirements", text: "Visa Requirements", level: 2 },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", text: "Insurance Requirements", level: 2 },
  { id: "recommended-providers", text: "Recommended Providers", level: 2 },
  { id: "costs", text: "Costs Breakdown", level: 2 },
  { id: "application", text: "Application Process", level: 2 },
  { id: "scenarios", text: "Real-World Scenarios", level: 2 },
  { id: "mistakes", text: "Common Mistakes", level: 2 },
  { id: "healthcare", text: "Healthcare in Barbados", level: 2 },
  { id: "faq", text: "FAQ", level: 2 },
  { id: "verdict", text: "Final Verdict", level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: "Caribbean Health Insurance Guide", href: "/countries/caribbean/insurance" },
  { title: "Insurance for Digital Nomads", href: "/insurance-for/digital-nomads" },
  { title: "Best Expat Health Insurance", href: "/best/expat-health-insurance" },
];

const requirementsColumns = [
  { key: "requirement", header: "Requirement" },
  { key: "details", header: "Details" },
  { key: "evidence", header: "Evidence Needed" },
];

const requirementsRows = [
  { requirement: "Annual Income", details: "$50,000+/year", evidence: "Employment letter, tax returns" },
  { requirement: "Remote Work", details: "Work for entity outside Barbados", evidence: "Employment contract or business registration" },
  { requirement: "Health Insurance", details: "Mandatory coverage valid in Barbados", evidence: "Insurance certificate" },
  { requirement: "Valid Passport", details: "Valid for duration of stay", evidence: "Passport copy" },
  { requirement: "Clean Record", details: "No criminal history", evidence: "Background check may be required" },
];

const insuranceColumns = [
  { key: "feature", header: "Coverage Feature" },
  { key: "minimum", header: "Barbados Requirement" },
  { key: "why", header: "Why It Matters" },
];

const insuranceRows = [
  { feature: "Medical Coverage", minimum: "Valid in Barbados", why: "Access to healthcare" },
  { feature: "COVID-19 Coverage", minimum: "Recommended", why: "May be checked at entry" },
  { feature: "Emergency Evacuation", minimum: "Strongly recommended", why: "Island location, specialized care may require travel" },
  { feature: "Coverage Duration", minimum: "Full visa period", why: "12 months typically" },
  { feature: "Hospitalization", minimum: "Included", why: "Private hospital costs are high" },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: "provider", header: "Provider" },
  { key: "coverage", header: "Coverage" },
  { key: "price", header: "Monthly Cost" },
  { key: "strengths", header: "Best For" },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: "SafetyWing", coverage: "$250,000", price: "$40-80", strengths: "Budget nomads" },
  { provider: "Cigna Global", coverage: "$1,000,000+", price: "$200-400", strengths: "Comprehensive coverage" },
  { provider: "Allianz Care", coverage: "$500,000+", price: "$180-350", strengths: "Global network" },
  { provider: "IMG Global", coverage: "$1,000,000", price: "$120-250", strengths: "Americas coverage" },
  { provider: "GeoBlue", coverage: "$1,000,000", price: "$150-300", strengths: "US expats" },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: "item", header: "Cost Item" },
  { key: "amount", header: "Amount (USD)" },
  { key: "notes", header: "Notes" },
];

const costRows = [
  { item: "Welcome Stamp Fee (Individual)", amount: "$2,000", notes: "12-month visa" },
  { item: "Welcome Stamp Fee (Family)", amount: "$3,000", notes: "Couple or family" },
  { item: "Health Insurance (Annual)", amount: "$500-4,000", notes: "Depends on coverage" },
  { item: "Background Check", amount: "$50-100", notes: "If required" },
  { item: "Document Courier", amount: "$50-100", notes: "If applicable" },
];

const timelineColumns = [
  { key: "step", header: "Step" },
  { key: "duration", header: "Timeline" },
  { key: "location", header: "Where" },
];

const timelineRows = [
  { step: "Prepare documents", duration: "1-2 weeks", location: "Home country" },
  { step: "Submit online application", duration: "1-2 hours", location: "Welcome Stamp portal" },
  { step: "Processing", duration: "5-7 business days", location: "Immigration department" },
  { step: "Receive approval", duration: "Via email", location: "Digital notification" },
  { step: "Pay fee", duration: "Immediate", location: "Online payment" },
  { step: "Travel to Barbados", duration: "At your convenience", location: "Any arrival port" },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Barbados Welcome Stamp 2025: Digital Nomad Visa Insurance & Complete Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Barbados Welcome Stamp digital nomad visa. Caribbean island living, $50,000 income requirement, 12-month stay, and step-by-step application."
  headline="Barbados Welcome Stamp: Insurance & Requirements Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about working remotely from the Caribbean—beach life meets location independence."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Qualifying Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  heroImage="/images/countries/barbados-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated January 2025
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Barbados Immigration
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Pioneer Program (Since 2020)
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Barbados launched the "Welcome Stamp" in July 2020, pioneering the modern digital nomad visa movement. This Caribbean island nation was among the first to create a dedicated pathway for remote workers—and it remains one of the most desirable destinations.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Imagine working with your toes in the sand, taking lunch breaks for snorkeling, and ending your workday with a rum punch at sunset. The Welcome Stamp makes this Caribbean dream legally accessible for a full year.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Barbados Welcome Stamp</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> 12 months (renewable)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Income requirement:</strong> $50,000+/year</li>
        <li>• <strong>Processing time:</strong> 5-7 business days</li>
        <li>• <strong>Insurance:</strong> Mandatory health coverage</li>
        <li>• <strong>Family-friendly:</strong> $3,000 covers entire family</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Barbados for Digital Nomads?</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Caribbean paradise:</strong> Pristine beaches, warm weather year-round</li>
      <li><strong>English-speaking:</strong> No language barrier—English is the official language</li>
      <li><strong>Safe and stable:</strong> One of the safest Caribbean islands with stable government</li>
      <li><strong>Good infrastructure:</strong> Reliable internet, modern amenities</li>
      <li><strong>US time zones:</strong> Eastern time zone ideal for Americas work</li>
      <li><strong>No local income tax:</strong> On foreign-sourced income during your stay</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Barbados is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ You earn $50,000+/year from remote work</li>
          <li>✓ You dream of Caribbean beach lifestyle</li>
          <li>✓ You work in US/Americas time zones</li>
          <li>✓ You value English-speaking environment</li>
          <li>✓ You appreciate safety and stability</li>
          <li>✓ You want to bring family ($3,000 covers all)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You have a tight budget (it's expensive)</li>
          <li>• You work European/Asian hours primarily</li>
          <li>• You prefer urban city lifestyle</li>
          <li>• You want very low cost of living</li>
          <li>• You dislike small island life</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Visa Requirements -->
  <section id="requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Welcome Stamp targets higher-earning remote workers with a $50,000/year threshold. This ensures applicants can afford Barbados's relatively high cost of living while contributing to the local economy.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={requirementsColumns} rows={requirementsRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Income Verification</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      You must demonstrate $50,000/year in remote work income. Accepted evidence includes:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Employment letter:</strong> Stating salary and remote work arrangement</li>
      <li><strong>Tax returns:</strong> Previous year showing income level</li>
      <li><strong>Bank statements:</strong> 3-6 months of consistent income</li>
      <li><strong>Business registration:</strong> For self-employed, plus revenue proof</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Family Application:</strong> Spouses and dependents are covered under the same application for $3,000 total—regardless of family size. Each family member must be included in the initial application.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Document Checklist</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Valid passport</li>
      <li>Passport-style photograph</li>
      <li>Proof of income ($50,000+/year)</li>
      <li>Proof of employment or business ownership</li>
      <li>Health insurance certificate</li>
      <li>Proof of relationship (for family applications)</li>
      <li>Completed online application form</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Coverage Must Be Valid in Barbados</h3>
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        Barbados requires health insurance valid during your stay. While no specific coverage minimum is mandated, comprehensive international health insurance is strongly recommended given Barbados's healthcare costs and island location.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Health insurance is mandatory for the Welcome Stamp. Your policy must cover you in Barbados for the full duration of your stay. Emergency evacuation coverage is particularly important given the island's location.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Coverage Recommendations</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Why Emergency Evacuation Matters</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Barbados is a small island. While it has good medical facilities for routine care, complex procedures or specialized treatments may require evacuation to the US, UK, or other locations. Evacuation by air ambulance can cost $50,000-100,000 without insurance.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Public Healthcare</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• <strong>Access:</strong> Queen Elizabeth Hospital available</li>
          <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Adequate for basic care</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cost:</strong> Subsidized but not free for visitors</li>
          <li>• <strong>Wait times:</strong> Can be long</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Private Healthcare</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• <strong>Access:</strong> Several private clinics</li>
          <li>• <strong>Quality:</strong> Modern, well-equipped</li>
          <li>• <strong>Language:</strong> English everywhere</li>
          <li>• <strong>Cost:</strong> High by Caribbean standards</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox variant="highlight">
    <p class="mb-4">Need health insurance for Barbados with evacuation coverage?</p>
    <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-white text-primary-700 font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-50 transition-colors" style="color: #1d4ed8 !important;">
      Compare Qualifying Plans →
    </a>
  </CTABox>

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      These providers offer comprehensive coverage suitable for Barbados's Welcome Stamp:
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Budget Nomads</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">SafetyWing at $40-80/month. Includes emergency evacuation which is crucial for island living.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">US Expats</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">GeoBlue. Strong Americas network, familiar to US residents, excellent Caribbean coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Comprehensive Global</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cigna Global. Full worldwide coverage with excellent evacuation benefits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Families</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Allianz Care. Good family plans with pediatric coverage and multi-member discounts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Costs Breakdown -->
  <section id="costs" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Welcome Stamp fee is straightforward: $2,000 for individuals, $3,000 for families. The bigger consideration is Barbados's high cost of living.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">First Year Total Cost Estimates</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Individual (Budget)</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">$2,600</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Visa + basic insurance</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Individual (Standard)</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">$4,500</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Visa + comprehensive insurance</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-2">Family</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900">$6,000+</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">Family visa + family coverage</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cost of Living in Barbados</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Barbados is expensive—one of the pricier Caribbean destinations. Most goods are imported, driving up prices. The $50,000 income requirement exists partly because you'll need it.
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Budget:</strong> $2,500-3,500/month (modest apartment, cooking mostly)</li>
      <li><strong>Comfortable:</strong> $4,000-6,000/month (nice apartment, dining out)</li>
      <li><strong>Premium:</strong> $8,000+/month (beachfront, full lifestyle)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Barbados offers one of the fastest, simplest digital nomad visa processes. The entire application is online, and most approvals come within a week.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Prepare passport, income proof, employment letter, and insurance certificate. All documents should be clear digital copies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Online Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Visit the official Welcome Stamp portal. Complete the form and upload all required documents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Processing</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Processing typically takes 5-7 business days. You may receive requests for additional documentation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Approval & Pay</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Once approved, you'll receive an email with payment instructions. Pay the $2,000 (or $3,000 for families) online.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Travel to Barbados</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Present your approval letter at immigration upon arrival. Your 12-month Welcome Stamp begins on entry.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Many nomads arrive first as tourists, explore the island, secure housing, then apply for the Welcome Stamp. You can apply from within Barbados.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Real-World Scenarios -->
  <section id="scenarios" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Here's how different situations typically play out with Barbados's Welcome Stamp:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Software Engineer, $120,000/year</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Remote for US company, wants Caribbean winter escape.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved in 5 days. Clear documentation, straightforward application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family of 4, $90,000/year combined</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Both parents remote, two school-age children.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved. $3,000 covered entire family. Children enrolled in international school.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Freelance Designer, $45,000/year</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Consistent clients but just below threshold.</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 font-medium">✗ Denied. $5,000 below the $50,000 minimum. Advised to increase income before reapplying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Marketing Director, $85,000/year</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Works US East Coast hours, perfect time zone alignment.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved quickly. Excellent fit for US-based remote work.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Startup Founder, variable income</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Some months $0, others $30,000. Total $70,000 last year.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved. Tax return showed $70,000 annual, exceeded threshold.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Couple, $110,000/year combined</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Both work remotely, no children, want beach lifestyle.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">✓ Approved as family unit for $3,000. Both meet income requirements individually anyway.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox>
    <p class="mb-4">Compare insurance plans for your Caribbean adventure—get quotes in minutes.</p>
    <a href="/get-quotes" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors" style="color: white !important;">
      Get Insurance Quotes →
    </a>
  </CTABox>

  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Barbados is expensive. Everything from groceries to rent costs significantly more than nearby islands or mainland Americas. Budget accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Skipping Emergency Evacuation Coverage</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">On a small island, serious medical situations may require evacuation. Air ambulance to the US can cost $50,000+. Make sure your insurance includes evacuation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Checking Internet at Accommodation</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">While Barbados has good infrastructure overall, internet quality varies by location. Test before committing to long-term rental. Fiber isn't everywhere.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting About Hurricane Season</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">June-November is hurricane season. While Barbados is south of the typical hurricane belt, tropical weather affects the island. Plan accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Family Members on Application</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">All family members must be included in the initial application. You can't add dependents later without starting a new application.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Mainland Amenities</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Barbados is a small island. Some products aren't available, shipping takes time, and selection is limited. Adjust expectations for island life.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Barbados -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
