    <p class="mb-4">
      Barbados has reasonable healthcare for the Caribbean, but it's a small island with limitations. For routine care, you'll find adequate facilities. For anything complex, evacuation may be necessary.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Medical Facilities</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Queen Elizabeth Hospital:</strong> Main public hospital, handles most conditions</li>
      <li><strong>Bayview Hospital:</strong> Private hospital, more comfortable but expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Sandy Crest Medical Centre:</strong> Private clinic, good for routine care</li>
      <li><strong>FMH Emergency Medical Clinic:</strong> 24/7 emergency services</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">What to Know</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li>All medical staff speak English</li>
      <li>Specialized care may not be available on-island</li>
      <li>Air ambulance to US/UK may be needed for serious conditions</li>
      <li>Pharmacies are well-stocked for common medications</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Sample Costs (Without Insurance)</h3>

