  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay Barbados taxes on my remote income?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The Welcome Stamp specifically allows you to work remotely without paying Barbados income tax on foreign-sourced income. You remain tax resident in your home country.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I open a Barbados bank account?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, Welcome Stamp holders can open local bank accounts. This is useful for local expenses, though most nomads keep their primary banking elsewhere.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Generally good but variable by location. Fiber is available in developed areas with speeds of 50-150 Mbps. Check connectivity before committing to housing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I bring my pet?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, but Barbados has strict import requirements including microchipping, vaccinations, and potentially quarantine. Plan well in advance—the process takes months.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the Welcome Stamp renewable?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. You can renew for additional 12-month periods as long as you continue to meet the requirements. Apply before your current stamp expires.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about schooling for children?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Barbados has several international schools offering British and American curricula. Fees are significant—budget $10,000-20,000/year per child.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

